Description:
  Generate or update a CFP for an event in an event series. When updating an
    existing CFP, pass the link or name of the existing CFP, and the values that
    are changing. The event-series is optional, and if not provided, the generator
    will attempt to find the series from the event.

Example:
  bin/rails generate cfp --event-series=rubyconf --event=rubyconf-2026

  This will create:
    - data/rubyconf/rubyconf-2026/cfp.yml

  To generate an ongoing meetup CFP for LRUG:
    bin/rails generate cfp --event=lrug-meetup --name "Want to speak at LRUG?" \
      --link "https://readme.lrug.org/#talks"

  To generate a lightning talk CFP for RBQConf 2026:
    bin/rails generate cfp --event=rbqconf-2026 --name "Lightning Talks" \
      --link "https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdVIotL2KY-ZLSCAa6tZfsYZGctnWBKwEfuAtrL4JDqmq6xOg/viewform" \
      --open-date "2026-02-20" --close-date "2026-02-26"

  To update a CFP and extend the close date:
    bin/rails generate cfp --event=rbqconf-2026 --name "Lightning Talks" \
      --close-date "2026-03-26"
